result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Ashten P Qualls

records.addlTxt: Order Appointing Counsel, signed and filed.

Defendant Ashten P Qualls appeared by video.  Prosecuting attorney Arthur Kenneth Thexton in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Indigency hearing proceeded.  Based upon the defendant's statements, the court found the defendant eligible for appointment of counsel at county expense.  
The court appointed Attorney Nicholas Weege to represent the defendant; counsel to be paid at the rate of $100.00 per hour. 
The court ordered the defendant to repay Milwaukee County for attorney fees at the rate of $50.00 per month beginning on 1/1/2023 and then the 1st of each month there after. Failure to make timely payments according to the imposed payment schedule may result in a civil judgment. 
Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense signed and filed. 
Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 30.
Status conference scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Ashten P Qualls in court.  Prosecuting attorney Ryan Jay Michaels in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Richards, Branch 30. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 30.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 4, 2022 at 08:30 am.

ADDRESS INFO for Ashten P Qualls
Current: 2415 W Congress St. #1, Milwaukee, WI 53209 United States  (Effective: 08-25-2022)
Prior: 4330 North 42nd Street, Milwaukee, WI 53216

Defendant Ashten P Qualls not in court.  Prosecuting attorney Catelin Ringersma in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. The forfeiture order is stayed for 30 days pending notice to the defendant. Court makes a finding that there is no possible victim identified, therefore, restitution is not an issue.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 9/14/22 @ 2p
